@startuml
title Activity Diagram: Execute Workflow

' Text Description:
' 1. The Engine receives an execution trigger for a specific workflow.
' 2. The system fetches the required Workflow Definition.
' 3. A new Workflow Instance is initialized.
' 4. The system identifies and starts the initial step.
' 5. The system enters a loop to process steps and evaluate next paths.
' 6. Once no more steps remain, the instance status is finalized.

start
:Receive execution trigger;
:Fetch Workflow Definition;
:Initialize Workflow Instance;
:Identify initial step;
repeat
  :Invoke Step Logic;
  :Determine next step;
repeat while (Is workflow finished?) is (no)
:Finalize Instance Status;
stop
@enduml